      "updated": 1780981703759,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Before ES6 - only one variable var.\nafter ES6 - three types of variable let, var, and const.\n\nProblems with var -\n\n-> Redeclaration allowed.\n\nvar a=5;\nvar a=6;\n\nconsole.log(a);\n\n-> functional scope.\n-> Loop related Problem.\n\n\n\nlet -> introduced in ES6.\n\n-> Redeclaration is not allowed.\n-> block scope.\n-> loop problem solved.\n\nconst\n\n-> reassignment is not allowed but in case of object it is allowed.\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20.225883214613948,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Before ES6 - only one variable var.\nafter ES6 - three types of variable let, var, and const.\n\nProblems with var -\n\n-> Redeclaration allowed.\n\nvar a=5;\nvar a=6;\n\nconsole.log(a);\n\n-> functional scope.\n-> Loop related Problem.\n\n\n\nlet -> introduced in ES6.\n\n-> Redeclaration is not allowed.\n-> block scope.\n-> loop problem solved.\n\nconst\n\n-> reassignment is not allowed but in case of object it is allowed.\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
