      "versionNonce": 652985307,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781069267230,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Scope means where a variable can be accessed from.\n\n-> Global Scope : \n\n-> Functional Scope : When a variable is defined inside a function, it cannot be accessed outside that function.\n\n-> Block Scope : \n\n-> Lexical means that the child function can access all the variables of its parent.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Scope means where a variable can be accessed from.\n\n-> Global Scope : \n\n-> Functional Scope : When a variable is defined inside a function, it cannot be accessed outside that function.\n\n-> Block Scope : \n\n-> Lexical means that the child function can access all the variables of its parent.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
