      "text": "-> Reconciliation – Comparing the old virtual DOM with the new virtual DOM and updating the DOM with minimal changes.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "-> Reconciliation – Comparing the old virtual DOM with the new virtual DOM and updating the DOM with minimal changes.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "dCAV4_ya4Pe_E_RxNtHKf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4151.065364767682,
      "y": 229.17650744036024,
      "width": 1148.7392578125,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bFh",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 940784115,
      "version": 76,
      "versionNonce": 1262904723,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781844896056,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "-> Diffing Algorithm - Diffing Algorithm in React JS differentiates the updated and previous DOM of the application. \n                           DOM stores the components of a website in a tree structure. \n                           React uses virtual DOM which is a lightweight version of the DOM. \n                           The only difference is the ability to write the screen like the real DOM, in fact, \n                           a new virtual DOM is created after every re-render.\n\n                        https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/reactjs/what-is-diffing-algorithm/",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "-> Diffing Algorithm - Diffing Algorithm in React JS differentiates the updated and previous DOM of the application. \n                           DOM stores the components of a website in a tree structure. \n                           React uses virtual DOM which is a lightweight version of the DOM. \n                           The only difference is the ability to write the screen like the real DOM, in fact, \n                           a new virtual DOM is created after every re-render.\n\n                        https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/reactjs/what-is-diffing-algorithm/",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
