    {
      "id": "w-ujrQ2-1x8ce54ObGaFd",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4101.773784898939,
      "y": 4443.347677189463,
      "width": 578.4395751953125,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bGo",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 725361719,
      "version": 208,
      "versionNonce": 256305431,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782363314458,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "in Js -\n\n<button\nonclick=\"Hello()\">click</button>\nor button.addEventListner\n\n-> In React js we will use CamelCase for defining any event\n    <button onClick={Hello}>click</button>",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "in Js -\n\n<button\nonclick=\"Hello()\">click</button>\nor button.addEventListner\n\n-> In React js we will use CamelCase for defining any event\n    <button onClick={Hello}>click</button>",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Q9V-jX1ygdeb_yWfNzZxy",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4041.2440258109104,
      "y": 4686.582573188937,
      "width": 277.9559020996094,
      "height": 35,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bGp",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1850920791,
      "version": 27,
      "versionNonce": 1250305463,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782363333633,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Synthetic Events =>",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Synthetic Events =>",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "duHlgugjFZprr4Qws6GjY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4123.784625468367,
      "y": 4739.960514774783,
      "width": 858.0394897460938,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bGq",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1025729527,
      "version": 510,
      "versionNonce": 1026424951,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782364130902,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "-> React will not directly use original event of browser.\n\n-> React will create a wrapper that will be known as Synthetic event.\n\n-> In case of normal js events, in different browser there can be different things,\n    but once we will use wrapper then it will hide these differences.\n\nwe don't need to call function at time of adding an event.\n\n<button onClick={hello()}> -> ye render hote hi chal jayega no need to click on enything.\n\n<button onClick={hello}> -> ye click hona ke baad chala ga.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "-> React will not directly use original event of browser.\n\n-> React will create a wrapper that will be known as Synthetic event.\n\n-> In case of normal js events, in different browser there can be different things,\n    but once we will use wrapper then it will hide these differences.\n\nwe don't need to call function at time of adding an event.\n\n<button onClick={hello()}> -> ye render hote hi chal jayega no need to click on enything.\n\n<button onClick={hello}> -> ye click hona ke baad chala ga.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
