      "updated": 1782795872103,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- to avoid mutiple state over a single components.\n\nSyntax -\n\nimport { useReducer } from \"react\"\n\nconst initialState = {\n  count: 0\n}\n\nfunction reducer(state, action) {\n  switch (action.type) {\n    case \"increment\":\n      return { count: state.count + 1 }\n\n    case \"decrement\":\n      return { count: state.count - 1 }\n\n    default:\n      return state\n  }\n}\n\nconst CounterUsingUseReducer = () => {\n  const [state, dispatch] = useReducer(reducer, initialState)\n\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <h1>{state.count}</h1>\n\n      <button onClick={() => dispatch({ type: \"increment\" })}>\n        Increment\n      </button>\n\n      <button onClick={() => dispatch({ type: \"decrement\" })}>\n        Decrement\n      </button>\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n\nexport default CounterUsingUseReducer",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- to avoid mutiple state over a single components.\n\nSyntax -\n\nimport { useReducer } from \"react\"\n\nconst initialState = {\n  count: 0\n}\n\nfunction reducer(state, action) {\n  switch (action.type) {\n    case \"increment\":\n      return { count: state.count + 1 }\n\n    case \"decrement\":\n      return { count: state.count - 1 }\n\n    default:\n      return state\n  }\n}\n\nconst CounterUsingUseReducer = () => {\n  const [state, dispatch] = useReducer(reducer, initialState)\n\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <h1>{state.count}</h1>\n\n      <button onClick={() => dispatch({ type: \"increment\" })}>\n        Increment\n      </button>\n\n      <button onClick={() => dispatch({ type: \"decrement\" })}>\n        Decrement\n      </button>\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n\nexport default CounterUsingUseReducer",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
